The framework’s registry is SQLite-backed but exercised in-memory for these packets, so the clean path is to generate the topology files, run the same migration/seed code, register the new files through `ArtifactRegistry`, and write the registry result into the proof/report. That gives the required “hash recorded” evidence without pretending there is a hidden persistent DB.
